courses.learning_outcomes:
After completing this course, students are expected to:
(1) understand the core concepts and technologies in Big Data, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning and Deep Learning;
(2) explain and analyse how these technologies are being applied to finance industry from asset management to insurance, and from customer service to regulatory and compliance areas;
(3) propose innovative AI solutions to financial industry to solve customers’ pain points and enhance their experience; and
(4) comprehend and be alert of the ethics and risks relevant to AI and machine learning.

Students are expected to be able to:
(1) understand bond market pricing conventions and quotations;
(2) derive a theoretical arbitrage-free bond price;
(3) formulate a fixed income portfolio investment/hedging strategy;
(4) tell different bond markets/sectors' characteristics;
(5) apply the rich information embedded in various term structure to economic analysis; and
(6) distinguish fixed income securities, as an asset class, unique return/risk profile from other financial securities.

Students are expected to be able to :
(1) identify the common motives behind mergers and acquisitions;
(2) evaluate the fair price to pay for the target;
(3) conduct the typical due diligence of a target firm;
(4) understand the integration process;
(5) understand the common risks behind acquisitions and steps to mitigate such risks.

After completing this course, students are expected to be able to demonstrate knowledge and understanding of:
• the purpose, limitations, layout and presentation of financial statements;
• cost analysis in the context of short and long term decision making and the use of discounted cash flow analysis;
• financial strategy including capital structure, dividend policy and corporate governance of firms;
• the importance of capital structure and dividend policy decisions;
• the assumptions underlying the preparation, interpretation and analysis of the Income Statement, Financial position statement and Cash Flow Statement.
